"{\"uid\": \"ealingtimes.co.uk-news-24484267.richards-insists-devastating-silver-will-olympic-learning-curve\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Sport Matt Richards vowed to use his 'devastating' Olympic silver medal as a crucial learning curve after missing out on gold by the barest of margins in Paris.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 161, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7, \"end\": 20, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Richards_(footballer,_born_1984)\", \"score\": 0.8167390230814645, \"rank\": 0.2243767313019458, \"text\": \"Matt Richards\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Richards_(footballer,_born_1984)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Richards_(footballer,_born_1984)\"}, {\"begin\": 155, \"end\": 160, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999982615009, \"rank\": 1.7385708819292721e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his 'devastating' Olympic silver medal\", \"from\": 33, \"to\": 71}, {\"ngram\": \"a crucial learning curve\", \"from\": 75, \"to\": 99}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 121, \"to\": 125}, {\"ngram\": \"margins\", \"from\": 143, \"to\": 150}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 21-year-old was pipped to a stunning men's 200m freestyle victory by an agonising 0.02s last night as Romanian David Popovici touched the wall a fraction in front of him.\", \"from\": 163, \"to\": 337, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 269, \"end\": 277, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romanian_language\", \"score\": 0.9992401002038104, \"rank\": 0.0004534532052955148, \"text\": \"Romanian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romanian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romanian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 278, \"end\": 292, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Popovici\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"David Popovici\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Popovici\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Popovici\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a stunning men's 200m freestyle victory\", \"from\": 193, \"to\": 232}, {\"ngram\": \"an agonising 0.02s\", \"from\": 236, \"to\": 254}, {\"ngram\": \"the wall\", \"from\": 301, \"to\": 309}, {\"ngram\": \"a fraction\", \"from\": 310, \"to\": 320}, {\"ngram\": \"front\", \"from\": 324, \"to\": 329}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Out in lane one, Richards produced a scintillating swim to give Popovici, a two-time world individual champion who goes by the self-labelled nickname of the 'Chlorine Daddy', a real scare at a raucous La Defense Arena.\", \"from\": 339, \"to\": 557, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"lane\", \"from\": 346, \"to\": 350}, {\"ngram\": \"Richards\", \"from\": 356, \"to\": 364}, {\"ngram\": \"a scintillating swim\", \"from\": 374, \"to\": 394}, {\"ngram\": \"Popovici\", \"from\": 403, \"to\": 411}, {\"ngram\": \"a two-time world individual champion\", \"from\": 413, \"to\": 449}, {\"ngram\": \"the self-labelled nickname\", \"from\": 462, \"to\": 488}, {\"ngram\": \"the 'Chlorine Daddy\", \"from\": 492, \"to\": 511}, {\"ngram\": \"a real scare\", \"from\": 514, \"to\": 526}, {\"ngram\": \"a raucous La Defense Arena\", \"from\": 530, \"to\": 556}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hardly anything could separate Popovici, Richards, bronze medallist Luke Hobson and fellow Brit Duncan Scott in a heart-thumping finale and despite the Team GB star thinking he touched the wall first, it was precocious Popovici, 19, who grabbed Olympic glory.\", \"from\": 559, \"to\": 818, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 627, \"end\": 631, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luke_Snyder\", \"score\": 0.7956363918217323, \"rank\": 0.2315682067758922, \"text\": \"Luke\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luke_Snyder\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luke_Snyder\"}, {\"begin\": 632, \"end\": 638, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Hobson\", \"score\": 0.9999999843471415, \"rank\": 1.56526558104326e-08, \"text\": \"Hobson\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Hobson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Hobson\"}, {\"begin\": 655, \"end\": 667, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duncan_Scott_(swimmer)\", \"score\": 0.9913273362707572, \"rank\": 0.004373974849644039, \"text\": \"Duncan Scott\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duncan_Scott_(swimmer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duncan_Scott_(swimmer)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Hardly anything\", \"from\": 559, \"to\": 574}, {\"ngram\": \"Popovici\", \"from\": 590, \"to\": 598}, {\"ngram\": \"Richards\", \"from\": 600, \"to\": 608}, {\"ngram\": \"a heart-thumping finale\", \"from\": 671, \"to\": 694}, {\"ngram\": \"the wall\", \"from\": 744, \"to\": 752}, {\"ngram\": \"precocious Popovici\", \"from\": 767, \"to\": 786}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic glory\", \"from\": 804, \"to\": 817}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Richards accepts full responsibility for not putting enough pressure on the pool's perimeter and believes suffering heartbreak from his 'technical' shortcomings can benefit him in the future.\", \"from\": 822, \"to\": 1013, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Richards\", \"from\": 822, \"to\": 830}, {\"ngram\": \"full responsibility\", \"from\": 839, \"to\": 858}, {\"ngram\": \"enough pressure\", \"from\": 875, \"to\": 890}, {\"ngram\": \"the pool's perimeter\", \"from\": 894, \"to\": 914}, {\"ngram\": \"heartbreak\", \"from\": 938, \"to\": 948}, {\"ngram\": \"his 'technical' shortcomings\", \"from\": 954, \"to\": 982}, {\"ngram\": \"the future\", \"from\": 1002, \"to\": 1012}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am over the moon but devastated at the same time,\\\" said Richards, who will now pivot his attention to the 100m freestyle event this week.\", \"from\": 1015, \"to\": 1155, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the moon\", \"from\": 1026, \"to\": 1034}, {\"ngram\": \"the same time\", \"from\": 1053, \"to\": 1066}, {\"ngram\": \"Richards\", \"from\": 1074, \"to\": 1082}, {\"ngram\": \"his attention\", \"from\": 1103, \"to\": 1116}, {\"ngram\": \"the 100m freestyle event\", \"from\": 1120, \"to\": 1144}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If anything I think that the silver is fantastic - it has made me hungry for more.\", \"from\": 1157, \"to\": 1240, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"anything\", \"from\": 1161, \"to\": 1169}, {\"ngram\": \"the silver\", \"from\": 1183, \"to\": 1193}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"An individual Olympic silver medal is massive for me - it's something that I have dreamt of since I was a little boy.\", \"from\": 1242, \"to\": 1360, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"An individual Olympic silver medal\", \"from\": 1243, \"to\": 1277}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 1303, \"to\": 1312}, {\"ngram\": \"a little boy\", \"from\": 1347, \"to\": 1359}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I'd be lying if I said that I wasn't dreaming of being one step higher on the podium, but tonight it wasn't meant to be.\", \"from\": 1362, \"to\": 1483, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the podium\", \"from\": 1437, \"to\": 1447}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is lots of lessons I can learn from the racing - I loved every minute of that tonight and it was a proper dogfight.\", \"from\": 1485, \"to\": 1607, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"lots\", \"from\": 1495, \"to\": 1499}, {\"ngram\": \"lessons\", \"from\": 1503, \"to\": 1510}, {\"ngram\": \"the racing\", \"from\": 1528, \"to\": 1538}, {\"ngram\": \"every minute\", \"from\": 1549, \"to\": 1561}, {\"ngram\": \"a proper dogfight\", \"from\": 1589, \"to\": 1606}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was a real battle that came down to the finish, and tonight I did not quite get my hand on the wall fast enough.\", \"from\": 1609, \"to\": 1725, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a real battle\", \"from\": 1617, \"to\": 1630}, {\"ngram\": \"the finish\", \"from\": 1649, \"to\": 1659}, {\"ngram\": \"my hand\", \"from\": 1693, \"to\": 1700}, {\"ngram\": \"the wall\", \"from\": 1704, \"to\": 1712}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It felt like [I touched the wall first] - I did think I'd done enough, but it's not a sport of subjection and black and white, it's down to numbers.\", \"from\": 1727, \"to\": 1876, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the wall\", \"from\": 1752, \"to\": 1760}, {\"ngram\": \"a sport\", \"from\": 1812, \"to\": 1819}, {\"ngram\": \"subjection\", \"from\": 1823, \"to\": 1833}, {\"ngram\": \"numbers\", \"from\": 1868, \"to\": 1875}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's down to my finish and technical ability to get the pressure into the wall.\", \"from\": 1878, \"to\": 1960, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my finish\", \"from\": 1894, \"to\": 1903}, {\"ngram\": \"technical ability\", \"from\": 1908, \"to\": 1925}, {\"ngram\": \"the pressure\", \"from\": 1933, \"to\": 1945}, {\"ngram\": \"the wall\", \"from\": 1951, \"to\": 1959}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If I got my hand on there first and did not put enough pressure through the board, that's not the board's fault, that's mine.\", \"from\": 1962, \"to\": 2088, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my hand\", \"from\": 1972, \"to\": 1979}, {\"ngram\": \"enough pressure\", \"from\": 2011, \"to\": 2026}, {\"ngram\": \"the board\", \"from\": 2035, \"to\": 2044}, {\"ngram\": \"the board's fault\", \"from\": 2057, \"to\": 2074}, {\"ngram\": \"mine\", \"from\": 2083, \"to\": 2087}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's something that I have got to work on, go back, learn from, improve on and make sure it does not' happen again.\\\"\", \"from\": 2090, \"to\": 2209, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 2098, \"to\": 2107}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Richards, who was crowned world champion over the distance at the age of just 20 in Fukuoka last year, added: \\\"I am young, I am 21 and I am planning on being in the sport for at least another 10 years yet, so every single one of these little lessons I can learn is hugely, hugely valuable.\\\"\", \"from\": 2211, \"to\": 2501, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2295, \"end\": 2302, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fukuoka\", \"score\": 0.999999199691367, \"rank\": 8.002146024975284e-07, \"text\": \"Fukuoka\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fukuoka\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fukuoka\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Richards\", \"from\": 2211, \"to\": 2219}, {\"ngram\": \"world champion\", \"from\": 2237, \"to\": 2251}, {\"ngram\": \"the distance\", \"from\": 2257, \"to\": 2269}, {\"ngram\": \"the age\", \"from\": 2273, \"to\": 2280}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 2372, \"to\": 2381}, {\"ngram\": \"these little lessons\", \"from\": 2440, \"to\": 2460}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As for Scott, whose four medals in Tokyo made him the most decorated British athlete at a single Olympics, he was unable to improve on his 200m freestyle silver from three years ago as he missed out on a medal by just 0.08s.\", \"from\": 2503, \"to\": 2727, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2510, \"end\": 2515, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Scott\", \"score\": 0.8082162498618068, \"rank\": 0.23729217045355028, \"text\": \"Scott\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Scott\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Scott\"}, {\"begin\": 2538, \"end\": 2543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.619623846607955, \"rank\": 0.6138818181554839, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"whose four medals\", \"from\": 2517, \"to\": 2534}, {\"ngram\": \"a single Olympics\", \"from\": 2591, \"to\": 2608}, {\"ngram\": \"his 200m freestyle silver\", \"from\": 2638, \"to\": 2663}, {\"ngram\": \"a medal\", \"from\": 2705, \"to\": 2712}, {\"ngram\": \"just 0.08s\", \"from\": 2716, \"to\": 2726}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Scottish star, 27, lost out to fellow Brit Tom Dean - who failed to qualify to defend his title at this Games - in Tokyo and delivered a below-par display in a choppy lane five.\", \"from\": 2729, \"to\": 2910, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2733, \"end\": 2741, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland\", \"score\": 0.9791884956373466, \"rank\": 0.02124727778185375, \"text\": \"Scottish\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland\"}, {\"begin\": 2776, \"end\": 2784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Dean_(swimmer)\", \"score\": 0.9999936593363623, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Dean\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Dean_(swimmer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Dean_(swimmer)\"}, {\"begin\": 2848, \"end\": 2853, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.619623846607955, \"rank\": 0.6138818181554839, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his title\", \"from\": 2819, \"to\": 2828}, {\"ngram\": \"this Games\", \"from\": 2832, \"to\": 2842}, {\"ngram\": \"-par\", \"from\": 2875, \"to\": 2879}, {\"ngram\": \"a choppy lane\", \"from\": 2891, \"to\": 2904}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Scott, who will also race in the 200m individual medley and relays here in Paris, said: \\\"I am pretty disappointed as you can probably imagine.\", \"from\": 2912, \"to\": 3054, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2912, \"end\": 2917, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Scott\", \"score\": 0.8082162498618068, \"rank\": 0.23729217045355028, \"text\": \"Scott\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Scott\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Scott\"}, {\"begin\": 2987, \"end\": 2992, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999982615009, \"rank\": 1.7385708819292721e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 200m individual medley\", \"from\": 2941, \"to\": 2967}, {\"ngram\": \"relays\", \"from\": 2972, \"to\": 2978}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Fourth is pretty tough for anyone - but I am really happy for Matt.\", \"from\": 3056, \"to\": 3124, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Fourth\", \"from\": 3057, \"to\": 3063}, {\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 3084, \"to\": 3090}, {\"ngram\": \"Matt\", \"from\": 3119, \"to\": 3123}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Maybe I saw myself as a little of an underdog tonight whereas last time I was a bit more of a favourite.\", \"from\": 3126, \"to\": 3231, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an underdog\", \"from\": 3161, \"to\": 3172}, {\"ngram\": \"a favourite\", \"from\": 3219, \"to\": 3230}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But I have been coming back strong this whole year - I have got to use that as an advantage, but it's a pretty tough one to swallow.\\\"\", \"from\": 3233, \"to\": 3367, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an advantage\", \"from\": 3313, \"to\": 3325}]}, {\"sen